{"questionId":"9085572","questionHtml":"<p>A standing wave is formed in a pipe open at one end and closed at the other. The length of the pipe is <em>L</em> and the speed of sound in the pipe is <em>V</em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/12d0156a4a079e3550210d5fa6d4b2b17a691cb8.png\"></p>\n<p><em>n</em> is a positive integer.</p>\n<p>What expression is correct about the frequencies of the harmonics in the pipe?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9085572","referenceCode":"23M.1A.SL.TZ1.14","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A standing wave is formed in a pipe open at one end and closed at the other. The length of the pipe is L and the speed of sound in the pipe is V. n is a positive integer. What expr","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"14","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["C. Wave behaviour","C.4 Standing waves and resonance"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}